      • determineTopLevelNodes

        public static java.util.Set<RootNode> determineTopLevelNodes(EffectiveModel model,
                                                             java.util.List<Compute> computeNodes,
                                                             java.util.function.Consumer<RootNode> onValidNode)
        Finds the top level nodes in a given topology
        Parameters:
        model - The effective model containing the topology that should get analyzed
        computeNodes - The list of Compute nodes for which the top level nodes should get determined
        onValidNode - Callback method that gets called if the node that currently processed by the iterator is valid. It does not only get called for every top level node
        Returns:
        the set of top level nodes for the given list of Compute nodes

      • buildTopologyStacks

        public static java.util.List<NodeStack> buildTopologyStacks(EffectiveModel model,
                                                            java.util.Set<RootNode> topLevelNodes,
                                                            java.util.Map<java.lang.String,KubernetesNodeContainer> nodes)
        Converts a set of top level nodes into a list of NodeStacks
        Parameters:
        model - The model containing the topology to perform the operations with
        topLevelNodes - The set of top level nodes for which the node stacks should be generated
        nodes - a map containing all nodes in the topology (key is the node name), the nodes are wrapped in the KubernetesNodeContainer class
        Returns:
        the resulting list of node stacks
